  "texts": [
    "Lastly, motivated by observations that language models \"avoid certain topics\" (Xu et al., 2021; Stuart-Ulin, 2018), the third requirement specifies that speakers should be open about any unwillingness to discuss topics or consider relevant advice.",
    "This property has also been described as \"evasiveness\" in the literature (Bai et al., 2022).",
    "Given the above requirements, there are numerous ways in which the maxim of transparency can be violated.",
    "A simple example is presented in Appendix A.6, Fig. 7.",
    "A key question is how the proposed maxims can be integrated, or operationalized, into current language models."
  ],
